Differential Methylation Analysis

NPT Huynh

20 October 2021

Abstract

Genomic DNA from CTR- and HD-derived glial progenitor cells were collected after 180 days of differentiation. Bisulfite-trated DNA was then hybridized on Infinium HumanMethylation 450 array. This vignette describes the analysis performed on .idat results.

PART1: Data import

Read in data

IDAT methylation results can be downloaded from GEO (GSE184518)

# Set up path for data directory
dataDirectory <- "./data/methylation/idat"
# Read in sample sheet
targets <- read.metharray.sheet("./data/methylation", pattern = "Sample_sheet.csv")
## [read.metharray.sheet] Found the following CSV files:
## [1] "./data/methylation/Sample_sheet.csv"
# Create cell line 
targets$line <- gsub("\\_.*", "", targets$Sample_Name)
# Create cell type
targets$CellType <- unlist(lapply(strsplit(targets$Sample_Name, "_"), function (x) x[2]))
targets$CellType <- gsub("\\(.*", "", targets$CellType)
# Create groups 
targets$Sample_Group <- rep(c("CTR", "HD"), each = 4)
# Reorder target group 
targets <- targets[order(targets$Sample_Group), ]
# Load the annotation data 
anno450k <- getAnnotation(IlluminaHumanMethylation450kanno.ilmn12.hg19)
# Read in cross reactive probes information for downstream filtering 
dataDirectory <- system.file("extdata", package = "methylationArrayAnalysis")
xReactiveProbes <- read.csv(file=paste(dataDirectory, "48639-non-specific-probes-Illumina450k.csv", sep = "/"), stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

# Raw data from IDAT files 
rgSet <- read.metharray.exp(targets=targets)
# Rename array 
sampleNames(rgSet) <- targets$Sample_Name

Quality control of samples

All samples passed detection p-values cut-off of 0.001, hence all of them were kept for downstream analyses.

# Detection p values. How much are we sure of the signals above background? 
detP <- detectionP(rgSet)
# Examine signals across samples to identify failed samples 

mean_detP <- as.data.frame(colMeans(detP))
colnames(mean_detP) <- "mdetP"
mean_detP$sample <- row.names(mean_detP)
mean_detP$group <- targets$Sample_Group
main_color <- c("black", "firebrick")
p <- ggplot(data = mean_detP, aes(x = sample,y = mdetP, fill = group)) + geom_col() 
p <- p +  ylab("Mean detection p-values") + xlab("") + theme_minimal()
p <- p + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust=1), legend.position = "bottom") 
p + scale_fill_manual(values = main_color) 

qcReport(rgSet, sampNames = targets$Sample_Name, sampGroups = targets$Sample_Group, pdf="./plots/qcReport.pdf")

PART2: Normalization and filtering of probes

Data exploration

Of the GPC between G19 (CTR) and G20 (HD), we do not expect global differences between these samples, thus preprocessQuantile was used.

mSetSq <- preprocessQuantile(rgSet)
## [preprocessQuantile] Mapping to genome.
## [preprocessQuantile] Fixing outliers.
## [preprocessQuantile] Quantile normalizing.
mSetRaw <- preprocessRaw(rgSet)
# Visualize data before and after normalization 
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
densityPlot(getBeta(mSetRaw), sampGroups = targets$Sample_Group, 
            main = "Raw", legend = FALSE, pal = main_color)
legend("top", legend = levels(factor(targets$Sample_Group)), text.col = main_color)
densityPlot(getBeta(mSetSq), sampGroups = targets$Sample_Group, 
            main = "Normalized", legend = FALSE, pal = main_color)
legend("top", legend = levels(factor(targets$Sample_Group)), text.col =main_color)

# MDS plots to examine sample variation
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
plotMDS(getM(mSetSq), top=1000, gene.selection="common", 
        col=main_color[factor(targets$Sample_Group)])
legend("topright", legend=levels(factor(targets$Sample_Group)), text.col=main_color,
       bg="white", cex=0.7)

Probe filtering

# Reorder probes so that detP and mSetSq are the same 
detP <- detP[match(featureNames(mSetSq), rownames(detP)),]
# Remove probes that failed in one more more samples 
keep <- rowSums(detP < 0.01) == ncol(mSetSq)
mSetSqFlt <- mSetSq[keep,]
# Data are two sisters, so skip the removing of sex chromosomes part 
# Remove probes with SNPs at CpG site
mSetSqFlt <- dropLociWithSnps(mSetSqFlt)
# Remove cross-reactive probes 
keep <- !(featureNames(mSetSqFlt) %in% xReactiveProbes$TargetID)
table(keep)
## keep
##  FALSE   TRUE 
##  27402 439972
mSetSqFlt <- mSetSqFlt[keep,]

Re-examine sample relationship after probe filtering

# MDS plots to examine sample variation
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
plotMDS(getM(mSetSqFlt), top=1000, gene.selection="common", 
        col=main_color[factor(targets$Sample_Group)])
legend("topright", legend=levels(factor(targets$Sample_Group)), text.col=main_color,
       bg="white", cex=0.7)

PART3: Probe-wise differential methylation analysis

M-values for statistics, and B-values for visualization

mVals <- getM(mSetSqFlt)
bVals <- getBeta(mSetSqFlt)
# Extract base means of mVals and bVals by group
mVals.df <- data.frame(row.names = row.names(mVals), 
                       G19=rowMeans(mVals[, 1:4]), 
                       G20=rowMeans(mVals[,5:8]))

bVals.df <- data.frame(row.names = row.names(bVals), 
                       G19=rowMeans(bVals[, 1:4]), 
                       G20=rowMeans(bVals[,5:8]))

DM analysis - per probes

condition <- factor(targets$Sample_Group)
design <- model.matrix(~0+condition, data = targets)
colnames(design) <- c("CTR", "HD")
design 
##   CTR HD
## 1   1  0
## 2   1  0
## 3   1  0
## 4   1  0
## 5   0  1
## 6   0  1
## 7   0  1
## 8   0  1
## attr(,"assign")
## [1] 1 1
## attr(,"contrasts")
## attr(,"contrasts")$condition
## [1] "contr.treatment"
# fit the linear model 
fit <- lmFit(mVals, design)
# create a contrast matrix 
contMatrix <- makeContrasts(HD-CTR, levels = design)
# contrast with bayesian 
fit2 <- contrasts.fit(fit, contMatrix)
fit2 <- eBayes(fit2)
summary(decideTests(fit2))
##        HD - CTR
## Down       5865
## NotSig   428003
## Up         6104

Get the table or results for the contrast

ann450kSub <- anno450k[match(rownames(mVals), anno450k$Name),c(1:4,12:19,24:ncol(anno450k))]
DMPs <- topTable(fit2, number = Inf, # return all genes
                 coef = 1, # column number 1 in the contrast matrix, this comes in handy in case of multiple comparisons 
                 genelist = ann450kSub, 
                 sort.by = "p") # sort by p values 
# Filter to get only the signif 
res <- DMPs[which(DMPs$adj.P.Val < 0.05), ]

Showing the first 1000 differentially methylated probes

htmltools::tagList(datatable(head(res[order(res$adj.P.Val),c(1:3,13,15,23,24,27)],1000),extensions="Buttons",options=list(dom="Bfrtip",buttons=c("csv"))))
